implement CET4 TEM4

动词读作 ˈɪmplɪˌmɛnt 。名词读作 ˈɪmplɪmənt 。 

1. V-T If you implement something such as a plan, you ensure that what has been planned is done. 实施; 执行 

例： The government promised to implement a new system to control financial loan institutions. 政府许诺要实施新的制度来控制金融贷款机构。 

2. implementation N-UNCOUNT 实施; 执行 

例： Very little has been achieved in the implementation of the peace agreement signed last January. 去年1月份签署的和平协议的执行几乎没有什么进展。 

3. N-COUNT An implement is a tool or other piece of equipment. 器具 [正式] 

例： ...writing implements. …书写用具。

